#Calculate the mean and median of columns 2 to 5, excluding 0 values.
statistics={}
for i in range(1,6):
   nozero= df[df.iloc[:,i]!=0].iloc[:,i]
   mean_nozero= nozero.mean()
   median_nozero= nozero.median()
   column_name= df.columns[i]
   statistics[column_name]={
      'mean':mean_nozero,
      'median':median_nozero
   }
   print(f"column:{column_name}")
   print(f"Mean is: {statistics[column_name]['mean']:.2f}")
   print(f"Median is: {statistics[column_name]['median']:.2f}")

Decision Tree

In[24]:
# Initialize the Decision Tree Classifier model
dt_model = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)

# Train the model on the training data
dt_model.fit(x_train, y_train)

# Predict the target variable on the testing data
y_pred_dt = dt_model.predict(x_test)

# Calculate the evaluation metrics
accuracy_dt = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_dt)
precision_dt = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_dt)
recall_dt = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_dt)
f1_dt = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_dt)

conf_matrix_dt = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_dt)
print(f'Confusion Matrix for Decision Tree Classifier:\n', conf_matrix_dt)  # 
tn, fp, fn, tp = conf_matrix_dt.ravel()
print(f'TP={tp}',f'TN={tn}',f'FP={fp}',f'FN={fn}')

specificity = tn / (tn + fp)if(tp+fp)!=0 else 0

# Display the evaluation metrics
results = []
results.append({
        'Model': 'Decision Tree Classifier',
        'Accuracy': accuracy_dt * 100,
        'Precision': precision_dt * 100,
        'Sensitivity (Recall)': recall_dt * 100,
        'Specificity': specificity * 100,
        'f1_score':f1_dt*100
    })
pd.DataFrame(results)

In[25]:
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc

y_predp= dt_model.predict_proba(x_test)

# Calculate the ROC curve and AUC for the decision tree model
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_predp[:, 1])

# Calculate AUC (Area Under Curve)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

#put result into dictionary
allrocauc[model_names[0]] = {'fpr': fpr, 'tpr': tpr, 'auc': roc_auc}

# plot ROC 
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'ROC curve (area = {roc_auc:.2f})')

# Draw a diagonal line 
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')

# set plot
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.02])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.title('ROC Curves for Decision Tree')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()

    'Importance': feature_importances_rf
})

        'Precision': precision_knn * 100,
